button.download.description: Text in button, which allows user to download the result

button.fast.description: Text in button, which allows user to set the 'fast speed' mode to fast to generate the image, must translate to 'Fast speed'

button.relax.description: Text in button, which allows user to set the 'slow speed' mode to relax to generate the image, must translate to 'Slow speed'

button.turbo.description: Text in button, which allows user to set the 'extreme speed' mode to turbo to generate the image, must translate to 'Extreme speed'

button.history.description: Text in button, which allows user to see the history of generated images

field.finalPrompt.description: Final Drawing prompt used to generate the image

field.elements.description: Drawing style used to generate the image

field.traceId.description: Trace ID for tracing the request of generating the image, do not translate it, keep it as 'Trace ID'

description.aspect.message: --aspect, Changes the aspect ratio of the generated image, default value depends on the model and mode

description.chaos.message: --chaos, Adjusts the degree of variation in the generated image, the higher the number, the more unique and unexpected the generated image, range is 0-100, default is 1

description.fast.message: Ignores current settings and runs a single generation task in 'fast speed' mode, no default value

description.iw.message: --iw, Sets the importance of image prompts relative to text prompts during the generation process, range is 0-2, default is 1

description.no.message: --no, Indicates the generation system to attempt to exclude certain elements, for example `--no plants` will attempt to generate images without plants, no default value
description.no.description: Description of the no parameter, translate it as 'Exclude'

description.quality.message: --quality, Sets the quality and rendering time of the generated image, range is .25, .5, or 1, default is 1

description.random.message: Adds a random base style code to the prompt, can use `--style random-16`, `--style random-64`, or `--style random-128` to get random style effects of different lengths, no default value

description.relax.message: Overrides current settings to run a single task in 'slow speed' mode, no default value

description.repeat.message: --repeat, Creates multiple tasks from one prompt, range is 1-40, default is 1

description.seed.message: --seed, Starting visual noise for generated images, range is 0-4294967295, default is randomly generated

description.stop.message: --stop, Stops the task at any stage of the generation process, range is 10-100, default is 100 (i.e., fully generated)

description.style.message: --style, switches between different versions or styles of Midjourney or Niji models, for example raw, cute, expressive, original, scenic, default value depends on the model and mode

description.stylize.message: --stylize, adjusts the intensity of the default aesthetic style of Midjourney applied in generation tasks, range is 0-1000, default is 100

description.tile.message: --tile, Generates an image that can be used for seamless tiling to create seamless patterns, no default value

description.turbo.message: Overrides current settings to run a single task in 'extreme speed' mode, no default value

description.weird.message: --weird, explores uncommon aesthetic styles with experimental nature, range is 0-3000, default is 0

description.translation.message: Enables automatic translation during generation, non-Chinese content will be automatically translated to English input for Midjourney

description.imageWeight.message: --iw, adjusts the weight of image prompts relative to text prompts, range is 0-2, default is 1

description.niji.message: --niji, When enabled, generated images will use the Niji model, producing anime-style images

description.uploadReferences.message: Upload images as references for generation, supports up to 5 images. If more than 1 image is uploaded, they will be automatically merged

description.raw.message: --raw, When enabled, generated images will use the Midjourney model, producing original style images

description.prompt.message: Enter commands, if additional parameters are added, they will override default preset parameters, e.g., adding `--stylize 200` will force the final command to use `--stylize 200`

action.generate.message: Click this button to start generating images

action.variation1.message: Adjust variation of the first image

action.variation2.message: Adjust variation of the second image

action.variation3.message: Adjust variation of the third image

action.variation4.message: Adjust variation of the fourth image

message.promptPlaceholder.message: Please enter a sentence to describe the image you want to generate, for example: a cute cat. Additional parameters will override default preset parameters
message.promptPlaceholder.description: Placeholder text in the prompt field

message.uploadReferencesExceed.message: You can upload up to 5 images at most
message.uploadReferencesExceed.description: Error message when the number of uploaded images exceeds the limit

message.uploadReferencesSuccess.description: Success message when images are uploaded successfully

message.uploadReferencesError.message: Failed to upload images, please try again later
message.uploadReferencesError.description: Error message when images fail to upload

message.startingTask.description: Message when the drawing task is starting

message.startTaskSuccess.description: Success message when the drawing task is started successfully

message.startTaskFailed.description: Error message when the drawing task fails to start

message.generating.description: Message when the image is being generated

message.noOperations.description: Message when there are no available operations

message.noTasks.message: No historical tasks, please start a new task first
message.noTasks.description: Message when there are no historical tasks

model.general.description: The name of a model which used for general image generation

model.niji.description: The name of a model which used for anime-style image generation, do not translate, keep it as 'Niji'

name.model.description: The model name, model is a term in machine learning, which is used to generate images

name.aspect.description: The name of the aspect parameter

name.ratio.description: The name of the ratio parameter

name.chaos.description: The name of the chaos parameter, translate is as 'rate of messy'

name.fast.description: The name of the fast mode, which is used to generate images quickly, translate it as 'Fast speed'

name.nijiStyle.description: The name of the nijiStyle parameter, do not translate it, keep it as 'Niji'

name.version.description: The name of the version parameter

name.imageWeight.description: The name of the imageWeight parameter

name.no.description: The name of the no parameter, which is used to exclude certain elements, translate it as 'Exclude'

name.quality.description: The name of the quality parameter, which is used to set the quality of the generated image

name.random.description: The name of the random parameter, which is used to add random style effects

name.relax.description: The name of the relax mode, which is used to generate images in 'slow speed' mode, translate it as 'slow speed'

name.repeat.description: The name of the repeat parameter, which is used to create multiple tasks from one prompt

name.seed.description: The name of the seed parameter, which is used to set the starting visual noise

name.stop.description: The name of the stop parameter, which is used to stop the task at any stage

name.style.description: The name of the style parameter, which is used to switch between different versions or styles of models

name.stylize.description: The name of the stylize parameter, which is used to adjust the intensity of the default aesthetic style

name.tile.description: The name of the tile parameter, which is used to generate images that can be used for seamless tiling

name.turbo.description: The name of the turbo mode, which is used to generate images in the 'Extreme speed' mode, translate it as 'Extreme speed'

name.weird.description: The name of the weird parameter, which is used to explore uncommon aesthetic styles, translate it as 'Weirdness'

name.translation.description: The name of the translation parameter, which is used to enable automatic translation during generation

name.advanced.description: The name of the advanced mode, which is used to enable advanced mode

name.niji.description: The name of the niji parameter, which is used to enable the Niji model, do not translate it, keep it as 'Niji'

name.ignore.description: The name of the ignore parameter, which is used to ignore certain elements

name.prompt.description: The name of the prompt parameter, which is used to enter drawing instructions

name.raw.description: The name of the raw parameter, which is used to enable the Midjourney model
